<br>
Plus having 2 Master Casting instructors looking over your shoulder made it that much worse. Andrew I have flown a twin engine plane into DFW in an thunder storm with a run away engine and a possible fire. There were fire trucks that met me on the runway and carried me and my wife to safety. I've had hail storms, ice, wing sheering turbulance, smoke, you name it. In all of those I was much more nervous taking that stupid casting test than I've ever been about anything in my life. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
